================================================================================
COMPARISON SUMMARY (SF50)
================================================================================
                    Streaming       Non-Streaming   Delta
CompactDetect       72517 ms        41 ms           -99.9% (pinned wins)
Run Generation      13119 ms        2214 ms         -83.1% (pinned wins, DMA vs page faults)
GPU Merge           606 ms          609 ms          ~same
CPU Gather          2230 ms         2452 ms         -8.9% (streaming slightly wins)
CPU Fixup           1612 ms         1762 ms         -8.5% (streaming slightly wins)
TOTAL SORT          17659 ms        7128 ms         -59.6% (non-streaming 2.5x faster)

Key finding: Streaming mode's mmap page-fault overhead devastates PCIe upload
performance (2.74 vs 16.26 GB/s for run generation). The GPU sort, merge, gather,
and fixup phases are comparable. The bottleneck is entirely in the H2D transfer
where streaming pays ~6x penalty from demand-paged reads vs pinned DMA.
